@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Blokop" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?

  At the start of a game, a coloured block is located on the upper left
of the board. The goal is to move that block to the lower right position.
Playing the game is very simple: just click on a block or doublet. If the
shape is next to the empty space, it will move towards the empty space.
Note that you can also use the cursor keys from the keyboard to move a
block or doublet.

  Sqaure blocks occupy one space on the board and can move horizontally
or vertically. On the other hand, doublets occupy two spaces, and they
can only move according to their shape: an horizontal doublet will move
horizontally and a vertical doublet will move vertically... that is, if
the empty space is in line and next to it...

  If you get stuck on one board, or a particular game is impossible to
complete, you can restart the game and Blokop will display a new board.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  -@{b}New Game@{ub}:                Restarts the game (or Left Amiga + "N").

  -@{b}Easy/Harder/Random Game@{ub}: Selects between the Easy, Harder or Random
                            game boards.

